SUMMARY:SRCC: Live in the Lounge with Corty Byron & the Light | The Wild Hymes | Christopher Bohn
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Joins the Conspiracy \n\n\n\nSomething’s brewing in Lancaster — and you’re invited. \n\n\n\nOn Saturday\, March 28th\, we’re bringing an evening of music\, live art\, and electric atmosphere to the city as part of the Susquehanna River Creative Conspiracy (SRCC). \n\n\n\nTwo acts. One unforgettable night. Corty & The Light bring gritty\, soulful blues-rock energy\, while The Wild Hymns offer haunting\, female-fronted alternative folk — intimate\, powerful\, and impossible to ignore. As the music plays\, local painters will be creating original works live\, letting sound and brushstroke feed each other in real time. \n\n\n\nThis is what the SRCC does — connecting artists\, musicians\, and community along the Susquehanna\, one event at a time. \n\n\n\nShow starts at 7 pm. Come hang. Feel the vibe. Join the conspiracy. \n\n\n\n$10 suggested donation.* \n\n\n\nCome hang. Feel the vibe. Join the conspiracy. \n\n\n\n*This event is donation based however space is limited. Secure your entry by donating in advance and your name will be added to the guest list.
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/srcc-live-in-the-lounge-with-corty-byron-the-light-the-wild-hymes-christopher-bohn/
LOCATION:The Lounge at Hempfield Apothetique\, 100 W Walnut St\, Lancaster\, Pennsylvania\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Music and Dance
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitlancastercity.com/wp-content/uploads/4b94edbd-932c-4ce8-b313-9fcd42e8ea6e.jpg
END:VEVENT
